e solvent's dielectric constant or the dipole moment. The magnitude of the solvation pressure, which is largest in water and smallest in 1,3-propanediol, varies with the square of the dipole potential as measured in monolayers in equilibrium with bilayers. {\textcopyright} 1989, American Chemical Society. All rights reserved.},
